    • updateAction

      public void updateAction​(UpdateMessage msg)
      Update the player status stated by the UpdateMessage and then gives the turn to the next player (always as stated by the message).

      A recap of what it does:

      • Set the market;
      • Set the available production cards pool;
      • Update with the card the playerId bought;
      • Update the playerId storage by removing spent resources and adding new ones;
      For more in depth structure of msg, see UpdateMessage class.
      Parameters:
      msg - message containing all the update information

    • playerCrashed

      public void playerCrashed​(int nextPlayerId)
      In case of a player's disconnection, set the player which turnNumber matches with nextPlayerId. If the latter is the one to whom the client app belongs, then start the regular turn. But if he/she is already in the middle of the turn, continue without restarting it.
      Parameters:
      nextPlayerId - id of the player which has to play the current turn
